# Academic Paper Writing

## Conference Paper (8 pages)
Abstract → Introduction (1p) → Related Work (1p) → Methodology (2-2.5p) → Experiments (2p) → Discussion (0.5p) → Conclusion (0.5p)

## Introduction: Funnel
Hook → Background → Gap → Approach → Contributions (bulleted, with numbers) → Organization

## Methodology Must-Haves
- Formal problem definition + notation
- Algorithm pseudocode (\begin{algorithm})
- Complexity analysis

## Experiments Must-Haves
- Setup: datasets, baselines, metrics, hardware
- Main results table (bold = best)
- Ablation table
- At least 1 analysis beyond main table

## Writing Rules
- Active voice: "We propose" not "A method is proposed"
- Quantify: "35% reduction" not "significant"
- Every claim = citation or experiment

## Revision Checklist
Every figure referenced + every table referenced + consistent notation + no placeholder text
